The Election Committee of the Nigerian Guild of Editors, (NGE) on Wednesday, said it had cleared 23 candidates for election into its Executive Council and Standing Committee. The election is to hold during its Biennial Convention scheduled for May 3, in Lagos. In a statement signed by the Secretary of NGE Electoral Committee, Mr Gbenga Ogunleye, in Lagos, the 23 candidates were cleared for 12 offices. Those cleared for the various electoral offices include: Mrs Funke Egbemode, cleared as Presidential candidate, while Messrs Umar Saidu and Chooks Ogbonnaya were cleared as contestants for the office of Deputy President. For Vice President (North), Hajia Sani and Sanusi Jibrin were cleared as contestants. Also, for Vice President (East), Mr Samuel Egbala and Mr Dom Isute, emerged as cleared contestants, while for the office of Vice President (West), Mr Mustapha Isa was cleared. Mary Atolagbe emerged as a successful candidate to contest for the post of General Secretary, while Austeen Elewodalu and Juliet Njiowhor were cleared as contestants for the post of Assistant General Secretary. Victoria Ibanga was cleared to contest for the post of Treasurer. while Ken Ugbechie was cleared to contest for the post of Social/Publicity Secretary. For the office of Standing Committee Members (North), the following were cleared as contestants: Catherine Agbo, Julius Idowu, Husseina Bangshika and Umoru Ibrahim. Also, for the office of Standing Committee Members (East), the following candidates were also cleared: Ngwoke A. Ngwoke, Ikpong Essien-Udom and Freston Akpor.